OL,3,C20 Days in Mariupol: Nurse recounts
OL,4,Cfinal days before Russian occupation
OL,6,F"There were no emotions, everyone was
OL,7,Fworking...and doing their job.
OL,8,FEmotions came later when we were
OL,9,Funable to resuscitate the child. " she
OL,10,Fsaid.
OL,12,F"Here was a child who had been killed
OL,13,Fin broad daylight."
OL,15,FBut despite the increasingly tense
OL,16,Fatmosphere as Russian troops
OL,17,Fsurrounded the city, Olena kept
OL,18,Fworking.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G5/13
