OL,3,C20 Days in Mariupol: Nurse recounts
OL,4,Cfinal days before Russian occupation
OL,6,FOn March 3 - as more bombs rained down
OL,7,Fon the city and also her home - Olena
OL,8,Fbrought her husband, daughter, and two
OL,9,Fyoung grandchildren, to live in the
OL,10,Fhospital.
OL,12,FHer grandchildren, aged 18 months and
OL,13,Fthree years old, slept on the hospital
OL,14,Ffloor in a small storage room.
OL,16,FMeanwhile, hospital patients and Olena
OL,17,Fherself slept in the corridors to stay
OL,18,Faway from windows in case they
OL,19,Fexploded.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G6/13
